# install.packages("tidymodels")
pacman::p_load("MLDataR",                                              # For Data
               "data.table", "magrittr",
               "tidymodels",
               "doParallel", "parallel")

registerDoParallel(cores=detectCores())


data(heartdisease)
data <- heartdisease %>%
  mutate(HeartDisease = ifelse(HeartDisease==0, "no", "yes"))


cols <- c("Sex", "RestingECG", "Angina", "HeartDisease")

data   <- data %>% 
  mutate_at(cols, as.factor)                                           #

3. Linear Kernel

3-1.

  • Workflow .
rec  <- recipe(HeartDisease ~ ., data = HD.train) %>%                  # recipe(formula, data)
  step_normalize(all_numeric_predictors()) %>%                         #      step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors(), one_hot = TRUE)                 #     -   NA

3-2.

  • .
    • (Type) (set_mode) (set_engine) .
      • :
        • Linear Kernel svm_linear() .
      • : Target
        • (Classification) (Regresssion) .
      • : Package
        • Linear Kernel Package kernlab LiblineaR .
  • Linear Kernel cost margin .
    • cost : cost
    • margin : SVM insensitive loss function epsilon (Only for Regression)
  • tune() .
svm.li.tune.mod <- svm_linear(cost = tune()) %>%                       # cost :          costNAset_mode("classification") %>%                                       # Target  (classification /  regression)NAset_engine("kernlab")                                                #   (kernlab /  LiblineaR) NA#     NAsvm.li.tune.mod %>% 
  translate()

Linear Support Vector Machine Specification (classification)

Main Arguments:
  cost = tune()

Computational engine: kernlab 

Model fit template:
kernlab::ksvm(x = missing_arg(), data = missing_arg(), C = tune(), 
    kernel = "vanilladot", prob.model = TRUE)

Caution! translate() svm.li.tune.mod Package kernlab ksvm() .

  collect_metrics() %>%
  filter(.metric == "roc_auc") %>%

4. Polynomial Kernel

4-1.

  • Workflow .
rec  <- recipe(HeartDisease ~ ., data = HD.train) %>%                  # recipe(formula, data)
  step_normalize(all_numeric_predictors()) %>%                         #      step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors(), one_hot = TRUE)                 #     -   NA

4-2.

  • .
    • (Type) (set_mode) (set_engine) .
      • :
        • Polynomial Kernel svm_poly() .
      • : Target
        • (Classification) (Regresssion) .
      • : Package
        • Polynomial Kernel Package kernlab .
  • Polynomial Kernel cost, margin, degree, scale_factor .
    • cost : cost
    • margin : SVM insensitive loss function epsilon (Only for Regression)
    • degree : Polynimial Degree
    • scale_factor : Polynomial Scaling Factor
  • tune() .
svm.po.tune.mod <- svm_poly(cost         = tune(),                         # cost :          costNA= tune(),                         # degree : Polynomial Degree
                            scale_factor = tune()) %>%                     # scale_factor : Polynomial Scaling Factor
  set_mode("classification") %>%                                           # Target  (classification /  regression)NAset_engine("kernlab")                                                    #   NA#     NAsvm.po.tune.mod %>% 
  translate()

Polynomial Support Vector Machine Specification (classification)

Main Arguments:
  cost = tune()
  degree = tune()
  scale_factor = tune()

Computational engine: kernlab 

Model fit template:
kernlab::ksvm(x = missing_arg(), data = missing_arg(), C = tune(), 
    kernel = "polydot", prob.model = TRUE, kpar = list(degree = ~tune(), 
        scale = ~tune()))

Caution! translate() svm.po.tune.mod Package kernlab ksvm() .

5. Radial Basis Kernel

5-1.

  • Workflow .
rec  <- recipe(HeartDisease ~ ., data = HD.train) %>%                  # recipe(formula, data)
  step_normalize(all_numeric_predictors()) %>%                         #      step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors(), one_hot = TRUE)                 #     -   NA

5-2.

  • .
    • (Type) (set_mode) (set_engine) .
      • :
        • Radial Basis Kernel svm_rbf() .
      • : Target
        • (Classification) (Regresssion) .
      • : Package
        • Radial Basis Kernel Package kernlab liquidSVM .
  • Radial Basis Kernel cost, margin, rbf_sigma .
    • cost : cost
    • margin : SVM insensitive loss function epsilon (Only for Regression)
    • rbf_sigma : Precision \((\gamma = \frac{1}{2\sigma^2})\)
  • tune() .
svm.rbf.tune.mod <- svm_rbf(cost      = tune(),                            # cost :          costNA= tune()) %>%                        # rbf_sigma : Precision (gamma = 1/2*sigma^2)
  set_mode("classification") %>%                                           # Target  (classification /  regression)NAset_engine("kernlab")                                                    #   (kernlab /  liquidSVM)NA#     NAsvm.rbf.tune.mod %>% 
  translate()

Radial Basis Function Support Vector Machine Specification (classification)

Main Arguments:
  cost = tune()
  rbf_sigma = tune()

Computational engine: kernlab 

Model fit template:
kernlab::ksvm(x = missing_arg(), data = missing_arg(), C = tune(), 
    kernel = "rbfdot", prob.model = TRUE, kpar = list(sigma = ~tune()))

Caution! translate() svm.rbf.tune.mod Package kernlab ksvm() .
